content.description: A 90 degree change from most of the area routes, few horizontal crimps here. Side pulls from old blast scars mark the crux at about 2/3 height.   Ends with some slopers after a mantle onto a ledge.
content.protection: 5 bolts, no chains on the anchors.
content.location: The right hand bolted line right in the center of the wall.

content.description: First 5 feet are a bit chossy. Follow the closely space bolts more or less straight up to the anchor. A balancy crux comes around bolt 4. Fun.
content.protection: 7 bolts to a two bolt anchor
content.location: Psychobikerbitch wall. Just left of (unknown or psychobitch)

content.description:
From Gorges Point follow cliff line 200 yards until it peters out. Walk back through brush to last 50' of cliff. From above head straight west from parking lot. New moderate route potential. Ground damp in spring and summer, worst place for skeeters on bluff, but total shade and rock quality is better than most other areas on bluff. 

  Take center line up, lots of side pulls.

Psychobitch Wall is the first wall you encounter. There is one line of bolts on this wall and as Bunsee stated is the namesake climb of this wall. There are a couple of variations left and right that one can do from the chain anchors. This area doesn't get as much light as the Adidas Wall and can be a little greasy at times. Avoid this wall after a good rain.
